node.text: When the curtain opened up and I saw a full crowd on its feet applauding - and it was the only sound for a few seconds - it was like a life recharge. Being there standing next to Lin Manuel and knowing that these giant  Broadway superstars were about to walk out and perform in front a crowd for the first time in a year and a half just set my emotions to 1000. But then - the confetti got me.  Confetti means it’s a celebration. So happy. So grateful. See you in September. We missed you Broadway.

Deer 🦌 readers, wood 🪵 you like to start reading our #FallonSummerReads book? Here’s a little bit of the plot of The Plot. No spoilers! Let us know your thoughts using #FallonSummerReads!

Ok, I’ll leaf 🍁 you alone now.

node.text:

What do you think so far? Stay tuned for more this week! #FallonSummerReads
